description:
**What:** Implement handle_relay_event() in event.rs — dispatches ClientEvent variants to AppState mutations, handling directory updates, message delivery, MLS group management, sealed sender, and reconnection lifecycle.

**Algorithm:**
1. Implement async fn handle_relay_event(state: &mut AppState, tx: &mpsc::Sender<JsonRpcRequest>, event: ClientEvent) -> anyhow::Result<()>:
2. Match event:
   - ClientEvent::Reconnecting { delay_secs }:
     state.connection = ConnectionState::Reconnecting { delay_secs };
     state.mls_active = false;
     state.online.clear(); state.online_seq.clear();
     state.mls_client = MlsClient::new(&state.my_pub_id)?; // reset ephemeral MLS
     state.room_hpke_secret = None;
     state.push_message(ChatLine::System(format!("[!] disconnected. reconnecting in {delay_secs}s...")));

   - ClientEvent::Reconnected:
     state.connection = ConnectionState::Connected;
     state.push_message(ChatLine::System("[!] reconnected".to_string()));

   - ClientEvent::Message(notif): dispatch on notif.method:
     - DIRECTORY_LIST → parse DirectoryListParams; rebuild state.online sorted by sequence; rebuild state.online_seq and nicknames maps; publish_key_package(state, tx).await?; publish_hpke_key(state, tx).await?; if !state.ever_connected { state.ever_connected = true; load_and_display_history(state).await?; } if state.my_pub_id == state.online.first().map(|u| u.pub_id.as_str()).unwrap_or("") { admin_create_group(state, tx).await?; }
     - USER_JOINED → parse UserJoinedParams; insert user at partition_point (maintaining ascending seq order) into state.online; state.online_seq.insert(pub_id.clone(), sequence); if !state.mls_active { publish_key_package(state, tx).await?; } if state.my_pub_id == state.online[0].pub_id && state.mls_active { admin_add_member(state, tx, pub_id).await?; }
     - USER_LEFT → parse UserLeftParams; retain in state.online; remove from state.online_seq;
     - USER_NICKNAME → parse; update state.nicknames;
     - DELIVER → parse DeliverParams; decrypt payload; push ChatLine;
     - SEALED_DELIVER → parse SealedDeliverParams; HPKE unseal; extract sender pub_id from first 64 bytes; decrypt MLS payload; push ChatLine;
     - WHISPER_DELIVER → parse WhisperDeliverParams; if not mls_active, try join_from_welcome; else decrypt;
     - SEALED_WHISPER_DELIVER → HPKE unseal with identity secret; handle whisper;
     - KEY_PACKAGE_READY → parse KeyPackageReadyParams; if admin: get_key_package_and_add(state, tx, pub_id).await?;
   - ClientEvent::Response(resp): match pending request by resp.id for GET_KEY_PACKAGE result etc.

3. Sub-functions:
   - async fn publish_key_package(state, tx): generate fresh KP bytes, send PublishKeyPackageParams.
   - async fn publish_hpke_key(state, tx): send state.hpke_identity_pub as PublishHpkeKeyParams.
   - async fn decrypt_payload(state, payload: Vec<u8>, sealed: bool) -> Result<Option<ClearMessage>>: MLS decrypt if active, else plaintext; deserialize ClearMessage; return Ok(None) for MLS commits.
   - async fn admin_create_group(state, tx): mls_client.create_group()?; state.mls_active = true; derive room_hpke from mls_client.room_hpke_keypair()?;
   - async fn admin_add_member(state, tx, pub_id): fetch KP, add via mls_client.add_member(), broadcast commit, whisper welcome.

**Defensive programming rules:**
- INVARIANT: never sort state.online in place — only read from it; rebuild from DirectoryList sorts naturally.
- Never deserialize relay payload in relay code — only in decrypt_payload (client side).
- publish_key_package uses mls_client.key_package_bytes()? — new KP each time.
- tx.send() errors: log warn, continue (relay may be gone).
- partition_point for USER_JOINED: use sequence field, not insertion time.
- Out-of-order events (USER_LEFT before USER_JOINED): guard with if let Some(pos) = online.iter().position.

**Agent team:** Standard (R+I+V). R reads cli/src/commands.rs event loop, core/src/protocol.rs method constants, core/src/mls.rs. I mirrors cli event dispatch logic adapted for TUI state. V runs cargo test -p nie-tui.

**Tests:**
- Test: Reconnecting clears online list and resets mls_active.
- Test: DirectoryList sets ever_connected.
- Test: USER_JOINED inserts at correct sorted position (sequence=5 between seq=3 and seq=7).
- Test: USER_LEFT removes correct entry.
- Test: decrypt_payload with plaintext JSON ClearMessage::Chat returns Some(Chat).
- Test: decrypt_payload with malformed bytes returns Err (handled gracefully, push System message).
